MPUMALANGA police are looking for killers who murdered a woman (33) in Machadodorp, Mpumalanga on 2 July. Brigadier Leonard Hlathi said police were informed of a vehicle parked next to the road in a veld near Rietfontein Farm with a woman inside, seemingly unconscious. “Police responded and rushed to the scene, where upon arrival found a yellow VW Polo with a woman in the driver’s seat with gunshot wounds. Medical personnel were notified about the incident and on arrival, the woman was certified dead. She was identified as Nompumelelo Patricia Malaza. According to her family, Nompumelelo, who was employed by a reputable bank in Sabie, was on her way to Carolina to visit her brother. A case of murder was opened and the matter is being investigated. The motive for the killing is unknown at this stage as nothing was stolen from the vehicle. Her belongings including wallets as well as her handbag and laptop were found inside the vehicle,” said Hlathi. Anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspects can contact Detective Sergeant Busani Mnisi on 082 798 0758 or call the Crime Stop number on 08600 10111. Alternatively, members of the public can send information via MYSAPSAPP, and information received will be treated as confidential and callers may opt to remain anonymous.